RT Explained with Examples and Derivation</h3><div class=\"flex items-center justify-between mt-auto pt-5 border-t border-slate-100\"><div class=\"flex items-center gap-2.5\"><div class=\"w-6 h-6 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 bg-amber-700 text-[10px]\">👩‍🔬</div><span class=\"text-[13px]\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);color:rgb(100, 116, 139)\">Dr. Sarah Kim</span></div><a class=\"text-blue-600 bg-transparent hover:bg-blue-50 px-4 py-2 -mr-4 rounded-full transition-all duration-300 text-[14px] flex items-center gap-1 group/read\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:500\" href=\"#\">Read<svg width=\"12\" height=\"12\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"translate-y-[1px] transition-transform group-hover/read:translate-x-1\"><line x1=\"5\" y1=\"12\" x2=\"19\" y2=\"12\"></line><polyline points=\"12 5 19 12 12 19\"></polyline></svg></a></div></div></div></div></div></section><section class=\"py-24 bg-[#f8fafc]\"><div class=\"max-w-[1000px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8\"><div class=\"text-center mb-16 flex flex-col items-center\" style=\"opacity:0;transform:translateY(20px)\"><h2 class=\"text-[clamp(28px,4vw,36px)] leading-[1.2] mb-5 tracking-tight\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:700;color:rgb(15, 23, 42)\">What Are Physics Fundamentals?</h2><p class=\"text-[16px] leading-[1.65] max-w-[700px]\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:400;color:rgb(100, 116, 139)\">Physics fundamentals are the core laws and principles describing how the universe behaves at every scale. Mastering them is the single most effective investment any science or engineering student can make.</p></div><div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6\"><div class=\"bg-white rounded-[16px] p-8 flex flex-col border border-slate-100 transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 hover:border-slate-200\" style=\"box-shadow:0 10px 40px -10px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);opacity:0;transform:translateY(30px)\"><h3 class=\"text-[18px] leading-[30px] mb-3\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:700;color:rgb(11, 18, 33)\">Classical Mechanics</h3><p class=\"text-[14px] leading-[1.7] flex-1 mb-8\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:400;color:rgb(100, 116, 139)\">Classical Mechanics begins with <span class=\"text-blue-500\">Newton&#x27;s three laws</span>. The <span class=\"text-blue-500\">second (F = ma)</span> relates force to mass and acceleration. The third states forces come in pairs. Together they predict everything from projectiles to orbits, and forces in structural engineering.</p><a class=\"text-blue-500 bg-transparent hover:bg-blue-50 px-4 py-2.5 -ml-4 rounded-full transition-all duration-300 flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.05em] uppercase w-fit group/link mt-auto\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans)\" href=\"#\">ALL MECHANICS ARTICLES<svg width=\"12\" height=\"12\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"transition-transform group-hover/link:translate-x-1\"><line x1=\"5\" y1=\"12\" x2=\"19\" y2=\"12\"></line><polyline points=\"12 5 19 12 12 19\"></polyline></svg></a></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-[16px] p-8 flex flex-col border border-slate-100 transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 hover:border-slate-200\" style=\"box-shadow:0 10px 40px -10px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);opacity:0;transform:translateY(30px)\"><h3 class=\"text-[18px] leading-[30px] mb-3\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:700;color:rgb(11, 18, 33)\">Waves &amp; Optics</h3><p class=\"text-[14px] leading-[1.7] flex-1 mb-8\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:400;color:rgb(100, 116, 139)\">Wave physics governs how energy propagates. <span class=\"text-blue-500\">Transverse waves</span> — oscillation perpendicular to propagation — include all electromagnetic radiation. The <span class=\"text-blue-500\">wave equation v = fλ</span> connects speed, frequency, and wavelength for every wave type in the universe.</p><a class=\"text-blue-500 bg-transparent hover:bg-blue-50 px-4 py-2.5 -ml-4 rounded-full transition-all duration-300 flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.05em] uppercase w-fit group/link mt-auto\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans)\" href=\"#\">ALL WAVES ARTICLES<svg width=\"12\" height=\"12\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"transition-transform group-hover/link:translate-x-1\"><line x1=\"5\" y1=\"12\" x2=\"19\" y2=\"12\"></line><polyline points=\"12 5 19 12 12 19\"></polyline></svg></a></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-[16px] p-8 flex flex-col border border-slate-100 transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 hover:border-slate-200\" style=\"box-shadow:0 10px 40px -10px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);opacity:0;transform:translateY(30px)\"><h3 class=\"text-[18px] leading-[30px] mb-3\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:700;color:rgb(11, 18, 33)\">Energy &amp; Thermodynamics</h3><p class=\"text-[14px] leading-[1.7] flex-1 mb-8\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:400;color:rgb(100, 116, 139)\"><span class=\"text-blue-500\">Energy</span> is the central concept connecting all physics. Conservation of energy — it cannot be created or destroyed, only transformed — is one of the deepest truths in science. The <span class=\"text-blue-500\">first law of thermodynamics</span> applies this to heat and work. The <span class=\"text-blue-500\">kinetic theory of gases</span> links molecular motion to pressure.</p><a class=\"text-blue-500 bg-transparent hover:bg-blue-50 px-4 py-2.5 -ml-4 rounded-full transition-all duration-300 flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.05em] uppercase w-fit group/link mt-auto\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans)\" href=\"#\">ALL THERMODYNAMICS ARTICLES<svg width=\"12\" height=\"12\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"transition-transform group-hover/link:translate-x-1\"><line x1=\"5\" y1=\"12\" x2=\"19\" y2=\"12\"></line><polyline points=\"12 5 19 12 12 19\"></polyline></svg></a></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-[16px] p-8 flex flex-col border border-slate-100 transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 hover:border-slate-200\" style=\"box-shadow:0 10px 40px -10px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);opacity:0;transform:translateY(30px)\"><h3 class=\"text-[18px] leading-[30px] mb-3\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:700;color:rgb(11, 18, 33)\">Forces &amp; Conservation Laws</h3><p class=\"text-[14px] leading-[1.7] flex-1 mb-8\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:400;color:rgb(100, 116, 139)\">Conservation laws are the deepest principles in physics. <span class=\"text-blue-500\">Conservation of momentum</span> governs every collision. <span class=\"text-blue-500\">Newton&#x27;s law of gravitation</span> describes the force between any two masses — from dropping a ball to the orbit of the Moon. These are exact laws with no known exceptions.</p><a class=\"text-blue-500 bg-transparent hover:bg-blue-50 px-4 py-2.5 -ml-4 rounded-full transition-all duration-300 flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.05em] uppercase w-fit group/link mt-auto\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans)\" href=\"#\">ALL FORCES ARTICLES<svg width=\"12\" height=\"12\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"transition-transform group-hover/link:translate-x-1\"><line x1=\"5\" y1=\"12\" x2=\"19\" y2=\"12\"></line><polyline points=\"12 5 19 12 12 19\"></polyline></svg></a></div></div></div></section><section class=\"py-24 bg-white\"><div class=\"max-w-[700px] mx-auto px-6\"><div class=\"text-center mb-12\" style=\"opacity:0;transform:translateY(20px)\"><span class=\"uppercase font-bold tracking-[0.2em] mb-4 block\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-size:11px;color:rgb(59, 130, 246)\">FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</span><h2 class=\"text-[clamp(28px,4vw,36px)] leading-[1.2]\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-instrument-serif);color:rgb(15, 23, 42)\">Common questions about physics fundamentals</h2></div><div class=\"flex flex-col\"><div class=\"border-b border-slate-100 transition-colors border-transparent\"><button class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-between py-5 text-left transition-all text-blue-600 bg-blue-50/50 border border-blue-400 rounded-lg px-4 -mx-4 mt-2 shadow-sm\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:600;font-size:15px\">What are the fundamentals of physics?<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-chevron-down w-4 h-4 text-slate-400 transition-transform rotate-180 text-blue-500\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m6 9 6 6 6-6\"></path></svg></button><div class=\"overflow-hidden\" style=\"height:0px;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pb-5 pt-2 text-slate-500 leading-relaxed text-[15px] px-0\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans)\">At its core, physics fundamentals include classical mechanics, electromagnetism, thermodynamics, and quantum mechanics. These form the basis for understanding everything from falling apples to stars.</div></div></div><div class=\"border-b border-slate-100 transition-colors \"><button class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-between py-5 text-left transition-all text-slate-800 px-0 hover:text-blue-600\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:600;font-size:15px\">Is Physics Fundamentals really free?<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-chevron-down w-4 h-4 text-slate-400 transition-transform\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m6 9 6 6 6-6\"></path></svg></button></div><div class=\"border-b border-slate-100 transition-colors \"><button class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-between py-5 text-left transition-all text-slate-800 px-0 hover:text-blue-600\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:600;font-size:15px\">Who creates the content on Physics Fundamentals?<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-chevron-down w-4 h-4 text-slate-400 transition-transform\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m6 9 6 6 6-6\"></path></svg></button></div><div class=\"border-b border-slate-100 transition-colors \"><button class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-between py-5 text-left transition-all text-slate-800 px-0 hover:text-blue-600\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:600;font-size:15px\">What topics does Physics Fundamentals cover?<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-chevron-down w-4 h-4 text-slate-400 transition-transform\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m6 9 6 6 6-6\"></path></svg></button></div><div class=\"border-b border-slate-100 transition-colors \"><button class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-between py-5 text-left transition-all text-slate-800 px-0 hover:text-blue-600\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:600;font-size:15px\">How is Physics Fundamentals different from a textbook?<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-chevron-down w-4 h-4 text-slate-400 transition-transform\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m6 9 6 6 6-6\"></path></svg></button></div><div class=\"border-b border-slate-100 transition-colors \"><button class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-between py-5 text-left transition-all text-slate-800 px-0 hover:text-blue-600\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-weight:600;font-size:15px\">What is the best way to learn physics fundamentals?<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-chevron-down w-4 h-4 text-slate-400 transition-transform\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m6 9 6 6 6-6\"></path></svg></button></div></div></div></section><section class=\"py-28 bg-[#0B1221] text-center\"><div class=\"max-w-[700px] mx-auto px-6\"><div style=\"opacity:0;transform:translateY(30px)\"><span class=\"uppercase font-bold tracking-[0.2em] mb-6 block\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans);font-size:12px;color:rgb(59, 130, 246)\">EARLY ACCESS</span><h2 class=\"text-[clamp(44px,5vw,56px)] leading-[1.1] mb-6\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-instrument-serif);font-weight:400;color:white\">Be first to experience<br class=\"hidden md:block\"/> Physics Fundamentals</h2><p class=\"text-[17px] leading-[1.65] mb-12 text-slate-400 font-normal\" style=\"font-family:var(--font-dm-sans)\">We&#x27;re building this platform in public. Sign up and you&#x27;ll get exclusive early access, weekly physics insights, and the chance to shape what we build next.</p><form class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center items-stretch gap-4 max-w-[550px] mx-auto mb-6\"><div class=\"relative flex-1\"><input typ